==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sainthood
<hw>Saint"hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being a saint; the condition of a saint.</def>
<rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The order, or united body, of saints; saints,
considered collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was supposed he felt no call to any expedition that might
endanger the reign of the military <qex>sainthood</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saintish</ent>⟦br⟧
